Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 02:38:51 +0200
Subject: slayzone: Phase 6.2 inline_tab_webview_ slot + TabStripModel wiring
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SlayzoneRegionContainer replaces mid's right pane (previously a single
50% browserchrome placeholder WebView) with a vertical BoxLayoutView that
stacks:
  - browserchrome placeholder (40px URL-bar strip, unchanged routing),
  - inline_tab_webview_: a native views::WebView with no chrome:// slot
    of its own, no entry in `regions_`, and no kRegionIds membership.

SlayzoneBrowserView inherits TabStripModelObserver, installs a
ScopedObservation on the Browser's TabStripModel at AddedToWidget, and
calls SetWebContents(active) both synchronously at wire-up time (to
catch the tab that already exists on normal Browser startup) and on
every non-selection-only change.

Phase 5.3 spike removed: MaybeSpikeTerminalSlot(),
--slayzone-spike-url, kSlayzoneSpikeDefaultUrl, and the PostTask dance
that deferred the spike until the first tab landed are all gone. The
terminal slot is back to its placeholder.

inline_tab_webview_ is a peer views::WebView owned by the view tree —
this is the final "Electron WebContentsView overlay, eliminated"
shape promised by Phase 6.
